latestIgtvVideos.caption:
FRIENDS!!!! 👋🏻👋🏻👋🏻
I started documenting my skincare/makeup journey because I desperately needed a creative outlet from my PhD program. Keeping up with this account has been amazing and has provided me with a much needed mental break! This is also the platform where I truly felt connected with the AAPI community. And in my ongoing effort to increase AAPI visibility in the beauty world, I’ve applied for the Sephora Squad! ✨

Sephora has a huge impact in the beauty space and I wish to use their platform to represent my beloved AAPI community. I’m passionate about purchasing from BIPOC-owned brands and organically posting about them. If selected, I intend on learning as much as I can about how I can continue to make a genuine impact. I’m also excited to deepen my understanding of the cosmetic world. 

I’ve been feeling compelled to apply for this and I’m glad that I did! If you read what I wrote and can vouch for any of it, I’d like to ask for your help to leave a short authentic “testimonial” from the link in my bio. That would be greatly greatly appreciated!!! 🤗💖

#sephorasquad #sephorasquad2022

latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Here is my review video of the Banish Collagen Booster Kit I purchased back in 2017. I started having hormonal/cystic acne a couple of months before I got married. So I needed something that would completely transform my skin, which is why I turned to @banishacnescars 💁🏻‍♀️ All to say I was more than happy with the results because my wedding makeup turned out FLAWLESS! 🌟

latestIgtvVideos.title: My Curology review after 6 months!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
For those who are curious about the brand @curology, this is my honest opinion about it! My personalized treatment bottle consisted of 2% Azelaic Acid, 1% Clindamycin, and 4% Niacinamide. The combination of these ingredients is suppose to treat acne, skin texture, and dark spots. If you’re thinking of trying the free trial, do it! I don’t regret doing it at all 😊
🎵Sunrise, icons8.com/music
